The paper is focused on the numerical computation of Nash equilibria in competitive two-player games, which is a topic that falls under the category of game theory (cs.GT). The paper also proposes a novel algorithm for this purpose, which involves optimization techniques (cs.LG) and machine learning (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper discusses the convergence properties of the algorithm, which is relevant to the field of numerical analysis (cs.NE) and control systems (cs.SY).
